This internal-use Curl Command Generator is a web-based tool designed to help Splunk administrators and consultants quickly craft API commands for interacting with knowledge objects via REST. Key capabilities include:
Support for GET, POST, and DELETE methods.
Optional Basic or Token Authentication.
A rich dropdown of ~50 Splunk API endpoints, including calculated fields, lookups, dashboards, and data models.
Instant curl command generation, reducing human error and saving hours for large-scale repetitive API testing.

Prepared by Jaswanth Reddy Nagu
